cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the measurement of interdisciplinarity in citation patterns among journals, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The specific example of applying the proposed diversity indicator to the citation patterns of journals in the information science and library science category also suggests a potential fit with cs.IR and cs.DL.
